.TH "LIGHTNING-CHANNEL-DRAIN" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-channel-drain \- check how much can be pushed out of a channel
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning channel-drain
.I channel_id
.SH DESCRIPTION
Returns the drain capacity of a channel: the local balance minus the
channel reserve, which is the maximum amount that can be pushed out
in a single payment.
.PP
Output:
.nf
{"channel_id":"...","local_sat":N,"pushable_sat":N,"local_ratio":F}
.fi
Returns
.nf
{"error":"not_found"}
.fi
when the channel is unknown.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-channel-balance (1),
.BR lightning-channel-list (1)
